---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Kernel - Daemon Core" description="The autonomous agent kernel. Orchestration, isolation, and coordination for multi-agent systems.">
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>Kernel</h1>
    <p class="hero-tagline">The orchestration layer for multi-agent intelligence.</p>
    <p class="hero-description">
      The Daemon Core kernel transforms raw AI capabilities into disciplined,
      coordinated agents. It provides the structural foundation: boot sequences,
      context management, safety boundaries.
    </p>
    <p class="hero-description">
      Not a chatbot. Not an interface. The deterministic substrate beneath
      agent computation.
    </p>
    <div class="hero-cta">
      <a href="/daemon/overview" class="btn-primary">Read Overview</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/stux-os/daemon-core-public" class="btn-secondary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        View Source
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="grid grid-2">
      <div class="feature">
        <h2>Structured Orchestration</h2>
        <p>
          Agents operate within defined parameters. They know their scope,
          their boundaries, and their coordination protocols.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature">
        <h2>Production Architecture</h2>
        <p>
          Designed for continuous operation. Session persistence, context
          management, and predictable behavior across restarts.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature">
        <h2>Vendor Isolation</h2>
        <p>
          Multiple AI providers operate under unified rules. Switch models
          without restructuring. No cross-contamination.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature">
        <h2>Safety Constraints</h2>
        <p>
          Boundaries are architectural, not optional. Permissions scale with
          environment trust. Humans remain in control.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2 class="section-title">Documentation</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-2">
      <a href="/daemon/overview" class="link-card">
        <h3>Overview</h3>
        <p>Core concepts and architectural rationale.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/daemon/architecture" class="link-card">
        <h3>Architecture</h3>
        <p>System structure, layers, and coordination.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/daemon/faq" class="link-card">
        <h3>FAQ</h3>
        <p>Common questions and clarifications.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/daemon/blog" class="link-card">
        <h3>Blog</h3>
        <p>Development updates and technical notes.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="status">
    <h2>Status</h2>
    <p>
      Kernel under active development. Specification stabilising through
      real-world deployment. Public materials reflect current direction.
    </p>
    <p>
      GitHub repository available for review and collaboration.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
